Idaho Wind Partners has 20 agreements with landowners for all of its projects, she said. Many of those landowners also raise cattle or sheep on the same land.\
"Our landowner agreement doesn't restrict what kind of livestock they can have," Gunn said.\
The animals don't cause problems, for the most part. But what has been an issue are the birds that live around the company's wind projects near the Milner Butte Landfill.\
"There's a high concentration of ravens in that area," she said.\
