There is a cap on how much Idaho Power will buy from the wind farms, but Gunn said the project doesn't typically exceed that cap.\
But for the last quarter, that wasn't the case. High output pushed the projects over the cap for two of the past for months, she said.\
Each wind turbine stands 262 feet to the nacelle -- the boxy section in the back of the turbine -- with 130-foot blades connected at the top. Sensors detect wind at 4- to 5- miles per hour and rotate the blades to catch the breeze. Generation can begin after wind speeds reach 6 miles per hour, Gunn said.\
